# Pokrovka, Fyodorovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Pokrovka () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative centre of Pokrovsky Selsoviet, Fyodorovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 195 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Pokrovka is located 20&nbsp;km northwest of Fyodorovka (the district's administrative centre) by road. Ilyinovka is the nearest rural locality.
